contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:33.131 --> 03:34.424
- Nice watch.
- Thanks.

03:34.924 --> 03:36.801
- What's the water resistance?
- 200 meters.

03:37.093 --> 03:38.928
- And it's got a date display?
- Yes, it does.

03:39.721 --> 03:41.973
I might have gone for a metal strap
instead of a leather strap.

03:42.056 --> 03:43.182
- Really?
- Yes.

03:44.017 --> 03:45.518
I think I'd prefer a metal strap.

03:46.519 --> 03:48.688
I've had this one for years.
It's as good as new.

03:48.771 --> 03:50.815
- What's the water resistance?
- 100 meters.

03:51.107 --> 03:52.817
- How long have you had it?
- Nine years.

03:53.818 --> 03:55.028
A little bored of it, actually.

03:55.737 --> 03:57.989
I've been thinking of getting a new one
for quite a while now.

03:58.072 --> 04:01.200
Okay, this is what we'll do.
We'll go to the place where I bought mine.

04:02.619 --> 04:04.162
If I tell them you're a colleague, a friend,

04:04.245 --> 04:05.663
they'll definitely give you a discount.

04:06.164 --> 04:08.750
Both the owner and his father have been
patients of mine for some time,

04:08.833 --> 04:11.294
so I know them quite well. Think about it.

04:25.600 --> 04:26.809
- Hi.
- Hi.

04:27.977 --> 04:31.147
Sorry to keep you waiting. Ah, did you eat?

04:31.564 --> 04:32.899
I just had some apple pie.

04:33.816 --> 04:36.986
Do you mind if I go grab something
to eat before we go? I'm starving.

04:37.070 --> 04:38.154
Sure. No problem.

04:39.030 --> 04:41.324
Are you sure you don't want anything?
Chicken wings or...

04:41.407 --> 04:44.327
No, thanks, I'm fine. Do you have money?
I can give you some.

04:44.410 --> 04:46.829
No, I've got money, thanks.
I'll be right back.

05:06.015 --> 05:08.476
- Did you get a haircut?
- Do you like it?

05:09.769 --> 05:10.728
Looks great.

05:14.399 --> 05:15.858
Aren't you going to eat your fries?

05:16.192 --> 05:18.361
- I'm saving them till last.
- Why?

05:19.237 --> 05:21.531
I really like fries.
I always save them for last.

05:22.323 --> 05:23.491
I do that, too.

05:38.297 --> 05:41.217
- Sorry I was late today, Steven.
- It doesn't matter.

05:42.385 --> 05:43.845
I was over at a friend's house.

05:44.429 --> 05:46.681
He got a new motorcycle.
I wanted to check it out.

05:47.724 --> 05:50.977
He took me for a ride. That's why I was late.

05:51.602 --> 05:52.729
It's fine.

05:53.896 --> 05:55.732
He even let me ride it for a little bit.

05:56.649 --> 05:57.900
I hope you were wearing helmets.

05:58.234 --> 06:02.155
Yeah, of course we were.
We weren't going very fast anyway.

06:12.165 --> 06:13.332
I got you a present.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.919
Oh, thank you very much. What is it?

06:17.962 --> 06:19.422
What is it?

06:26.095 --> 06:27.346
It's very nice.

06:29.474 --> 06:30.683
Can I give you a hug?

06:34.937 --> 06:36.105
Thank you very much.

06:45.782 --> 06:48.242
- That's fantastic.
- It's water resistant

06:48.326 --> 06:50.787
- up to 200 meters.
- Does this come off?

06:51.496 --> 06:52.663
I prefer a leather strap.

06:52.872 --> 06:56.042
It comes off, yes.
You can put on any strap you like.

06:57.001 --> 06:59.712
But metal are more hard-wearing,
that's why I got you the metal strap.

06:59.796 --> 07:01.047
It's more expensive, too.

07:04.967 --> 07:06.052
- Hey, Dad.
- Hmm!

07:06.135 --> 07:07.845
Do you remember Claire,
my friend from school?

07:08.721 --> 07:10.348
- Yes.
- It's her birthday

07:10.431 --> 07:12.558
and she's having
a party in two weeks, at her place.

07:12.934 --> 07:16.187
- Most of the class are invited. Can I go?
- We'll see.

07:17.355 --> 07:20.900
Dad, if Kim goes to the party,
can I go with her?

07:21.526 --> 07:22.443
I don't know, darling.

07:22.527 --> 07:24.237
Your mother and I will discuss it
and we'll see.

07:24.654 --> 07:27.490
I'd say they can go.
Claire is a very nice girl.

07:27.573 --> 07:29.450
She's the girl you met at the mall
with her parents

07:29.534 --> 07:31.160
who asked about becoming a doctor.

07:31.744 --> 07:33.538
She's the one who wants to be a cardiologist.

07:34.288 --> 07:35.748
Yes, I remember.

07:37.500 --> 07:38.709
How was work today?

07:40.711 --> 07:43.047
Fine. How about you?

07:43.631 --> 07:45.967
I've decided to make some changes
at the clinic.

07:47.301 --> 07:49.720
I think I'm gonna get it painted
and buy a new couch.

07:50.388 --> 07:52.348
Look at you all hunched over like that.

07:53.015 --> 07:55.726
How many times do I have to tell you,
you'll strain your back?

07:56.394 --> 07:58.646
Your hair is practically trailing
in your food.

07:58.729 --> 08:02.316
Bob, you promised me you'd get a haircut
and you still haven't done it.

08:02.400 --> 08:04.485
- I'll get a haircut.
- Tomorrow.

08:06.571 --> 08:08.739
Not tomorrow, Dad. After the party.

08:10.533 --> 08:13.494
I like his hair long. He has lovely hair.

08:14.328 --> 08:16.664
- What about mine?
- You have lovely hair, too.

08:17.123 --> 08:18.499
We all have lovely hair.

08:21.043 --> 08:22.753
I bought that dress that you liked.

08:24.880 --> 08:26.090
I'll wear it for you tomorrow.

08:26.173 --> 08:29.510
I can't show it to you now, it needed
alterations. I'm picking it up tomorrow.

08:29.969 --> 08:32.304
- The black one?
- It was the black one you liked,

08:32.388 --> 08:33.806
- wasn't it?
- Yes.

08:34.056 --> 08:37.476
The other one looked great on you, too.
But I think the black one was perfect.

08:37.559 --> 08:38.852
I'm worried it's a little too short.

08:38.936 --> 08:40.895
I'd like it better if it were below the knee.

08:41.105 --> 08:43.691
You look amazing,
however long or short the dress is.

08:44.442 --> 08:47.945
Tomorrow I'm gonna bake a lemon cake
and nobody's gonna eat any of it but you.

08:48.404 --> 08:49.530
Not even the kids?

08:50.156 --> 08:52.700
- Not even the kids.
- Poor kids.

08:53.159 --> 08:57.038
Did I tell you Bob announced the other day
that he wants to be an ophthalmologist?

08:57.121 --> 08:58.289
Yes, you did.

08:58.539 --> 09:00.333
Bob would be a coal miner
if you were one, too.

09:01.959 --> 09:03.336
Could you turn on some more light, please?

09:15.306 --> 09:16.432
General anesthetic?

09:17.224 --> 09:18.225
General anesthetic.

09:50.383 --> 09:51.467
How's that?

09:53.344 --> 09:54.261
Perfect.

11:14.717 --> 11:16.218
- Martin.
- Yeah.

11:20.556 --> 11:23.601
Look, I've told you, best not to come
to the hospital without calling me first.

11:24.101 --> 11:28.147
I know, you're right. I'm sorry.
I just wanted to thank you again.

11:28.647 --> 11:31.066
And to show you my new strap
I got for my watch.

11:31.525 --> 11:35.654
I, uh, exchanged the, uh, metal strap
for a leather one.

11:37.281 --> 11:40.910
I'm sorry, I didn't mean to put you
in this awkward position.

11:42.953 --> 11:43.954
Goodbye.

11:45.456 --> 11:47.374
Martin. Come here.

11:49.543 --> 11:50.961
What kind of strap did you get?

11:51.170 --> 11:52.922
- Brown leather.
- Show me.

11:56.217 --> 11:57.676
- It's very nice.
- You think so?

11:57.760 --> 11:59.678
- Or are you just saying that?
- No, I really like it.

12:01.138 --> 12:03.891
Next time you want to come here,
please call me first. You have my number.

12:04.475 --> 12:05.643
It's for your own good.

12:06.227 --> 12:08.896
I might be with a patient, or in surgery,
or in a meeting.

12:09.438 --> 12:11.482
There's no point in you waiting around
if I can't see you.

12:11.690 --> 12:13.234
It's for your own... Good morning.

12:13.317 --> 12:15.402
Good morning, Steven,
I have those test results.

12:15.861 --> 12:17.112
Shall I leave them on the desk?

12:17.196 --> 12:18.447
Please do. Yeah, I'll take a look at them

12:18.531 --> 12:19.406
- in a minute.
- All right.

12:19.490 --> 12:20.783
We've got the same watch.

12:22.034 --> 12:23.035
Let me introduce you.

12:23.953 --> 12:28.123
This young man, is one of my daughter's
school mates.

12:29.542 --> 12:32.461
I ran into Martin and his parents
at the mall last week.

12:33.337 --> 12:35.089
He told me he's very interested in medicine.

12:35.881 --> 12:37.633
- He wants to be cardiologist.
- Ah...

12:38.467 --> 12:39.969
I suggested he stop by sometime...

12:41.095 --> 12:43.222
so he can see what being
a doctor's really about.

12:43.889 --> 12:45.850
Martin, this is Matthew.
Great friend of mine.

12:46.267 --> 12:47.768
And an excellent anesthesiologist.

12:48.644 --> 12:49.812
That's great.

12:51.939 --> 12:53.107
Nice to meet you.

12:54.191 --> 12:57.528
Nice to meet you, too.
Let me know when you're ready.

13:03.325 --> 13:04.368
I've got to go back in now.

13:05.077 --> 13:07.079
We'll talk on the phone to arrange
our next meeting. All right?

13:07.162 --> 13:08.414
Okay. Goodbye.

13:40.362 --> 13:42.448
I think your breathing's really
improved over the last three months.

13:42.948 --> 13:44.909
That's what the choir director said, too.

13:44.992 --> 13:46.744
Did you tell her to move
you closer to the front?

13:46.827 --> 13:49.330
Yes, I did.
She said she'd see what she can do.

13:50.122 --> 13:51.332
Bob, did you water the plants?

13:51.874 --> 13:53.083
Mum said she would water them.

13:53.375 --> 13:54.460
Your mother works very hard.

13:55.085 --> 13:57.087
That's why we said it would be nice
to help out all that we can.

13:57.588 --> 13:59.465
And we agreed that Kim would take care
of walking the dog.

13:59.924 --> 14:01.300
And you would take care of the plants.

14:03.302 --> 14:05.638
How about I walk the dog
and Kim can do the plants?

14:06.305 --> 14:08.724
You're too young to be wandering
around at night, by yourself.

14:10.935 --> 14:12.978
- Thanks for the brush.
- You're welcome.

14:14.063 --> 14:15.230
We have to go.

14:16.732 --> 14:19.276
Tell Bob to water the plants now
that the sun has gone down.

14:19.360 --> 14:21.904
I watered them already.
Come on, we're gonna be late.

14:23.530 --> 14:25.032
- Goodnight, darling.
- Goodnight.

14:38.796 --> 14:42.341
A full 40 years have passed
since the German cardiologist,

14:42.424 --> 14:46.011
Andreas Gruentzig, performed
the first coronary angioplasty

14:46.345 --> 14:49.515
on September 16th, 1977.

14:51.308 --> 14:53.686
Today, that first patient
is still alive and well.

14:53.769 --> 14:57.189
Doctor Gruentzig, however,
had an unfortunate accident

14:57.564 --> 14:59.900
and met with an untimely end.

15:00.442 --> 15:03.570
In short, he is one of those rare cases
where we can say:

15:04.154 --> 15:05.823
"The operation was a success...

15:06.782 --> 15:07.783
but, unfortunately,

15:08.492 --> 15:11.745
the doctor didn't make it".

15:15.708 --> 15:20.004
In the four decades that have passed
since that first coronary angioplasty,

15:20.087 --> 15:21.171
many things have changed.

15:21.547 --> 15:24.967
A new wave of techniques
and scientific breakthroughs have...

15:25.050 --> 15:27.011
I'm going for a cigarette.
I'll be at the bar.

15:27.094 --> 15:29.430
- Okay.
- ...endovascular aortic surgery

15:29.847 --> 15:32.683
and new treatments
for heart failure that include

15:32.766 --> 15:36.729
stem cell therapy, left ventricular
remodeling and, by all indications,

15:36.812 --> 15:40.065
the rapidly expanding use
of mechanical circulatory support.

15:41.275 --> 15:43.444
The guy that made it told me what was in it.

15:43.527 --> 15:46.739
And now I can't remember now,
but it is very refreshing.

15:47.489 --> 15:49.742
- Would you like one?
- No, thank you.

15:50.784 --> 15:52.870
Just try it. It's really delicious.

15:52.953 --> 15:54.830
You can use this straw. I haven't touched it.

15:55.497 --> 15:57.291
He hasn't had a drink in three years.

15:57.875 --> 16:01.128
- High GGTs and elevated transaminases.
- Oh, good on you

16:01.211 --> 16:02.296
for not drinking.

16:02.379 --> 16:04.923
Well, I wouldn't say no
to a cocktail if you're offering.

16:05.007 --> 16:06.592
Of course. I'll get you one right away.

16:07.134 --> 16:08.761
- We should go soon.
- Yeah.

16:08.844 --> 16:10.846
- It's early.
- He's got surgery in the morning.

16:10.929 --> 16:12.848
- He needs to get some sleep.
- It's still early.

16:13.057 --> 16:14.224
We've got surgery in the morning.

16:14.308 --> 16:15.225
Fine, okay.

16:16.477 --> 16:18.687
- How are the kids?
- They're doing very well.

16:18.771 --> 16:22.399
Bob has started piano lessons.
The teacher says he's very talented.

16:22.983 --> 16:25.319
Now we have to get him one
so he can practice at home.

16:25.402 --> 16:28.072
I just haven't gotten around to it yet.
I'm renovating the clinic.

16:28.530 --> 16:30.866
- I'm on the phone all day.
- Our daughter started menstruating

16:30.949 --> 16:32.868
- last week.
- Great.

16:32.951 --> 16:35.245
Yes, she was a little scared
but she's okay now.

16:35.704 --> 16:37.664
- You haven't seen her in ages.
- Not since last summer

16:37.748 --> 16:38.791
at the school choir...

16:39.208 --> 16:40.084
recital.

16:40.167 --> 16:42.294
You and Mary should come
over one night for dinner.

16:42.795 --> 16:45.798
You really shouldn't stay late, either.
Drink that cocktail you've ordered.

16:45.881 --> 16:48.008
Get yourself home.
You've gotta be at the hospital

16:48.092 --> 16:51.386
- in six hours. Time to go, darling?
- Yes.

16:51.470 --> 16:52.930
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight, Matthew.

16:56.433 --> 16:58.769
- Oh, it was a good night.
- I think so.

17:07.944 --> 17:09.154
Do you have many friends?

17:10.280 --> 17:11.323
Not that many.

17:13.075 --> 17:15.202
I don't think people can have
a lot of friends.

17:16.161 --> 17:17.538
I mean, it's difficult.

17:19.205 --> 17:23.042
The most important thing in life is
to have good friends, not lots of friends.

17:25.796 --> 17:26.964
That's what my dad used to say.

17:28.382 --> 17:30.926
- Your father was absolutely right.
- Yes, I know.

17:32.761 --> 17:35.055
I have a very good friend
who plays basketball in school.

17:35.931 --> 17:37.391
Sometimes we play it together.

17:41.019 --> 17:43.063
I also consider my mom to be a friend.

17:44.273 --> 17:47.317
I know it might sound strange
but ever since my father died, we...

17:47.401 --> 17:50.237
we... we've been very close, me and my mom.

17:52.781 --> 17:54.950
We talk about things. Lots of things.

17:56.243 --> 17:58.245
She helps me as much as she can
with a lot of stuff.

17:59.371 --> 18:00.372
I help her too.

18:03.417 --> 18:06.420
I'd like to ask you a favor.
Only if you want to, of course.

18:07.254 --> 18:09.173
I don't want you
to feel pressured or obliged.

18:09.256 --> 18:12.050
It just seemed to me like
a good idea, so I thought I'd ask.

18:14.553 --> 18:18.223
I'd like you to come by my house one day
to meet my wife and children.

18:20.017 --> 18:22.936
I think you'll get along great.
What do you think?

18:44.708 --> 18:46.418
Good afternoon. You must be Martin.

18:46.668 --> 18:50.505
- That's right. You must be Anna.
- That's right.

18:51.256 --> 18:54.635
These flowers are for you.
Your husband told me you like orchids,

18:54.718 --> 18:58.722
but I couldn't find
any fresh cut ones so I brought you roses.

18:59.348 --> 19:00.599
How do you like roses?

19:01.016 --> 19:04.519
Thank you very much, Martin.
I love roses. That's very kind of you.

19:05.520 --> 19:09.483
Come on in.
Steven is waiting for you in the yard.

19:19.284 --> 19:21.328
- This is Bob.
- Very nice to meet you.

19:22.162 --> 19:23.205
And this is Kim.

19:23.664 --> 19:26.625
Very nice to meet you.
I brought you some little gifts.

19:26.917 --> 19:28.168
That's very kind of you.

19:28.794 --> 19:32.673
It's a key ring with a musical note on it
for Kim because I know she likes music.

19:34.967 --> 19:37.302
And one with a smiley face for Bob.

19:38.595 --> 19:41.181
- What do we say, Bob?
- Thanks.

19:43.934 --> 19:44.851
How lovely...

19:46.061 --> 19:48.355
Well, we should probably eat.

19:48.438 --> 19:50.941
- Are you hungry, Martin?
- I'm starving.

19:55.862 --> 19:57.948
How long have you been in the choir, Kim?

19:58.907 --> 20:02.786
Two years. Since I was 12.
Do you like singing?

20:03.578 --> 20:06.623
I love it, but I haven't got
a very good voice.

20:08.959 --> 20:10.794
- How old are you?
- 16.

20:12.212 --> 20:14.089
Have you got hair under your arms yet?

20:14.339 --> 20:16.883
- Yes.
- I just got my first period.

20:21.513 --> 20:24.433
- Do you mind if I light a cigarette?
- You'd better not.

20:24.766 --> 20:27.144
It's all right. Just go over by the window.

20:38.488 --> 20:39.948
Can you sing us something?

20:41.283 --> 20:42.826
What, now?

20:42.909 --> 20:44.494
Yes. Anything you like.

20:45.287 --> 20:46.872
No. Not right now.

20:47.873 --> 20:51.752
- She's embarrassed.
- No, I'm not. Just don't feel like it.

20:53.003 --> 20:54.421
When did you start smoking?

20:54.963 --> 20:57.883
About eight months ago.
I was over at a friend's place.

20:58.216 --> 20:59.634
It was a party, actually.

21:00.344 --> 21:04.014
And this girl offered me a cigarette
and I said, "Why not," and lit up.

21:07.017 --> 21:08.977
That was a mistake. I regret it.

21:10.103 --> 21:12.856
But it's too late now. I'm addicted.

21:14.691 --> 21:16.151
Can you show me the hair under your arms?

21:17.027 --> 21:17.944
Sure.

21:21.948 --> 21:23.075
You haven't got that much.

21:24.076 --> 21:25.702
Have you seen how hairy my dad is?

21:26.453 --> 21:27.371
No.

21:27.537 --> 21:30.374
He's got three times more hair than you do.

21:32.834 --> 21:36.088
- You've got a great body.
- Thanks.

21:40.175 --> 21:43.220
Do you wanna go out for a walk?
It's a nice day.

21:45.680 --> 21:47.391
I'd rather stay here and listen to music.

21:49.476 --> 21:53.355
- Is that my MP3 player or yours?
- Mine, and don't you dare take

21:53.438 --> 21:54.398
this one and lose it, too.

21:55.607 --> 21:57.234
What kind of music do you listen to?

21:57.984 --> 22:02.739
- All kinds.
- I'm into metal and punk. What about you?

22:03.281 --> 22:05.909
I think it's worth listening
to all kinds of music.

22:07.035 --> 22:09.037
Depends on my mood and what I'm doing.

22:10.330 --> 22:12.207
I'll come for a walk with you if you want.

22:12.958 --> 22:14.876
We can take the dog with us
if you don't mind.

22:15.961 --> 22:18.422
I'd prefer it if it was just the two of us.

22:19.297 --> 22:21.007
I get nervous around dogs...

22:22.050 --> 22:25.137
in case they get into a fight
with another dog.

22:25.720 --> 22:28.473
The idea of separating dogs fighting
scares me.

