23:54.643 --> 23:56.186
Is this homemade lemonade?

23:56.853 --> 23:58.647
- Yes.
- It's amazing.

23:59.439 --> 24:03.026
My mom makes lemonade, too.
She hasn't made it in a while, though.

24:03.235 --> 24:06.613
I'll ask her to make some. I love lemonade.

24:08.073 --> 24:12.202
I'd like to meet your mother.
And we can have a lemonade contest.

24:12.786 --> 24:14.037
She'd like that.

24:15.038 --> 24:17.874
The kids' rooms are amazing.
So big and bright.

24:19.501 --> 24:21.336
You're welcome to spend the night
if you want.

24:22.170 --> 24:24.464
We can easily fit a mattress
on the floor next to Bob's bed.

24:24.923 --> 24:27.759
You two can hang out in the morning
and I'll drop you home tomorrow afternoon.

24:28.093 --> 24:30.345
Thank you very much, but I'd rather not.

24:30.971 --> 24:34.266
I gotta get home tonight.
I don't like leaving my mom by herself.

24:36.101 --> 24:39.271
- Whatever you want.
- Where did you two go?

24:40.313 --> 24:43.316
- Just for a walk.
- I love this neighborhood.

24:43.984 --> 24:46.319
So quiet, clean, beautiful.

24:47.529 --> 24:48.780
Where do you live, Martin?

24:49.322 --> 24:53.076
We live in a not-so-nice neighborhood
in a not-so-nice house.

24:54.077 --> 24:55.745
Up... up... uh, up north.

24:59.124 --> 25:02.544
- What a charming boy.
- Isn't he?

25:04.671 --> 25:08.341
Yes, very. How did his father die?

25:09.884 --> 25:14.180
Car crash. Driving home.
Smashed into a pole. Killed instantly.

25:15.765 --> 25:16.975
How long have you known him?

25:17.809 --> 25:20.270
Quite some time.
He was a patient of mine years ago.

25:22.897 --> 25:25.900
- Did you go to the funeral?
- I did go, yes.

25:27.277 --> 25:28.528
Why didn't I go with you?

25:30.155 --> 25:32.490
I think I told you about it,
but you were busy or something.

25:39.789 --> 25:41.583
You should tell him to come round again.

25:42.000 --> 25:43.918
I will. He'll be great company for Bob.

25:44.294 --> 25:47.088
I thought next time I could take both
of them out somewhere, for a bike ride.

25:48.340 --> 25:50.258
You should get that.
It could be the hospital.

25:56.598 --> 25:59.684
- Hello?
<i>- Hello. How are you?</i>

26:01.936 --> 26:05.106
I'm fine, Martin. Is something wrong?

26:05.899 --> 26:08.193
<i>No, I just called to tell you I had...</i>

26:08.276 --> 26:09.944
<i>a wonderful time today.</i>

26:10.945 --> 26:12.280
I'm very pleased to hear that.

26:13.031 --> 26:16.576
<i>Yes. I thought I should return the favor.</i>

26:16.660 --> 26:20.705
<i>So I'd like to invite you to dinner,
at my house.</i>

26:21.081 --> 26:25.168
<i>My mom will be delighted to see you.
She hasn't seen you in two years.</i>

26:25.877 --> 26:29.464
<i>Not since the hospital. She'll make meatloaf.</i>

26:30.632 --> 26:32.175
That's very kind of you.

26:32.967 --> 26:34.052
We'll do that someday.

26:34.469 --> 26:36.763
<i>Tomorrow night. I told her already.</i>

26:37.263 --> 26:39.265
<i>I've asked her to make meatloaf and lemonade.</i>

26:40.266 --> 26:43.937
<i>I'll be home by 6:30. Around 7:3Ã˜?</i>

27:17.387 --> 27:19.013
Did you come by the hospital today?

27:19.347 --> 27:23.685
No. I was in school.
And then I went to the gym.

27:24.352 --> 27:25.979
Weren't you down at the hospital today?

27:26.438 --> 27:29.107
I was, but I was really busy.

27:29.190 --> 27:31.401
I just wondered whether you came by
and couldn't find me.

27:35.071 --> 27:37.282
I thought we could all
watch a movie together.

27:38.575 --> 27:39.492
If you don't mind.

27:40.410 --> 27:41.745
I'd like to watch a movie.

27:42.328 --> 27:46.082
I'm sorry, I have to be getting home soon.
I can't be out too late.

27:46.750 --> 27:49.544
I didn't tell my wife I'd be late tonight
and she might get worried.

27:50.587 --> 27:51.671
You could call her.

27:52.547 --> 27:55.175
Anyway, if you feel tired,
you could stop the movie.

27:55.258 --> 27:58.094
You could go home and we could watch
the rest next time you come.

27:58.178 --> 28:01.806
Please, it's my favorite movie.
It's also my father's favorite movie, too.

28:03.850 --> 28:05.852
<i>Special today is blueberry waffles.</i>

28:06.644 --> 28:08.980
<i>- Why are you telling me this?</i>
<i>- Because I want you</i>

28:09.063 --> 28:10.064
<i>to believe in me.</i>

28:10.774 --> 28:13.401
<i>You're not a god.
You can take my word for it.</i>

28:13.485 --> 28:15.320
<i>This is 12 years of Catholic school talking.</i>

28:16.070 --> 28:17.822
<i>I could come back if you're not ready.</i>

28:18.281 --> 28:20.825
<i>How do you know I'm not a god?</i>

28:20.909 --> 28:22.535
I think I'll go to bed.

28:24.704 --> 28:26.915
I'm sorry I can't watch the rest
of the movie with you.

28:31.377 --> 28:33.880
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight, Martin.

28:36.841 --> 28:39.761
<i>...groundhog, who, as legend has it,
can predict the coming of an early spring.</i>

28:40.970 --> 28:43.389
<i>So I guess the question we have
to ask ourselves today is...</i>

28:44.557 --> 28:45.975
Have you been married long?

28:47.352 --> 28:48.353
16 years.

28:57.195 --> 29:00.114
- You have lovely hands.
- Thank you.

29:01.157 --> 29:07.080
Most doctors have beautiful hands.
So white and soft and clean.

29:07.413 --> 29:09.040
- Really?
- Yes.

29:12.418 --> 29:15.129
I remember your hands from back
when I used to visit my husband

29:15.213 --> 29:16.297
at the hospital.

29:17.715 --> 29:20.051
In fact, I even told him about your hands.

29:21.094 --> 29:22.095
And he agreed.

29:23.096 --> 29:26.432
"You're right," he said.
"He has beautiful hands."

29:28.601 --> 29:29.769
Thank you very much.

29:31.938 --> 29:33.606
Do you remember me coming to the hospital?

29:34.691 --> 29:35.608
Of course.

29:37.235 --> 29:39.821
I was a little heavier then
and my hair was brown.

29:40.905 --> 29:41.823
Yes.

29:43.741 --> 29:47.203
I got tired of it.
I dyed it about a month ago.

29:48.997 --> 29:52.041
Did you prefer me with brown hair?
Like it was back then?

29:54.168 --> 29:56.170
I think it's... nicer now.

29:56.921 --> 29:58.089
Yes, I agree.

30:09.517 --> 30:12.145
Would you like some dessert?
I made a caramel tart.

30:13.605 --> 30:14.606
No, thank you.

30:14.939 --> 30:18.693
Maybe later then. You did have a lot to eat.

30:29.329 --> 30:31.247
Can I take a closer look at your hands?

30:52.268 --> 30:55.688
Don't worry, he's definitely asleep.
There's nothing to be afraid of.

30:56.147 --> 30:58.483
In any case, he wants this as much as I do.

30:58.566 --> 31:01.611
- I have to go.
- I'm sorry if I made you feel awkward.

31:01.694 --> 31:02.904
I didn't mean to.

31:03.946 --> 31:06.324
But I won't let you leave
until you've tried my tart.

31:06.991 --> 31:09.285
Please, I'll get you a piece now.
Please, sit down.

31:09.369 --> 31:12.080
I'm sorry, I really have to go. Goodnight.

31:34.435 --> 31:35.561
Good morning.

31:36.062 --> 31:37.980
What are you doing here?
Why aren't you in school?

31:38.064 --> 31:40.775
- My heart aches.
- What do you mean?

31:42.735 --> 31:45.738
I'm in pain. My chest, it hurts.

31:46.447 --> 31:50.326
- My heart. I'm worried.
- There's no need for you to be worried.

31:52.787 --> 31:55.957
I'm worried because it's hereditary.

31:56.624 --> 31:59.669
- You're too young to be worried.
- That's what you said about my father.

32:00.670 --> 32:04.549
He didn't smoke. He ate a very healthy diet.

32:06.300 --> 32:08.136
He went swimming almost every day.

32:09.512 --> 32:12.265
He should have come out of that surgery
alive but he died.

32:15.226 --> 32:18.646
I smoke. I started smoking recently.

32:22.442 --> 32:23.443
It hurts here.

32:31.075 --> 32:33.119
I hardly slept at all last night.

32:34.745 --> 32:37.331
My mom was so worried, I slept in her bed.

32:55.224 --> 32:58.811
If I had hair on my chest and belly,
how would you attach these?

32:59.812 --> 33:01.022
We'd shave the hair off first.

33:02.231 --> 33:04.317
How long does it take for the hair
to grow back?

33:04.901 --> 33:05.818
I don't know.

33:07.111 --> 33:08.779
About a month, I suppose.

33:11.449 --> 33:14.368
Your son told me that you've got
lots of hair under your arms.

33:14.827 --> 33:16.245
Three times more than I do.

33:16.871 --> 33:20.208
And that you've got a very hairy back
and a very hairy belly.

33:21.375 --> 33:24.003
I probably do have a little more hair
than you do because I'm older than you.

33:25.254 --> 33:28.591
But soon you'll have more hair, too.
It's all down to hormones.

33:29.842 --> 33:31.010
Can you show me, please?

33:32.386 --> 33:35.431
Can you take off your shirt
and show me, please?

33:37.767 --> 33:38.684
Please.

34:02.416 --> 34:05.461
Okay, you do have more hair than I do
but not three times more.

34:06.045 --> 34:08.839
Me and my mom thought it would be nice
if you came by for dinner tonight.

34:10.049 --> 34:11.717
We could watch the rest of the movie.

34:13.261 --> 34:14.679
Does eight sound good for you?

34:15.554 --> 34:17.764
That's very kind of you
but I just can't make it tonight.

34:19.308 --> 34:20.226
I need to be at home.

34:20.726 --> 34:23.980
- Can't you get away for a couple of hours?
- I can't. No.

34:25.231 --> 34:26.148
Some other time.

34:27.108 --> 34:28.484
My mom's gonna be upset.

34:29.318 --> 34:32.196
Can I tell you a secret?
But don't tell her I told you.

34:33.531 --> 34:37.784
I think she... I think she likes you.
I mean, she's attracted to you.

34:38.369 --> 34:41.289
But she says that's not true.
But it is, I'm sure.

34:42.415 --> 34:44.875
And, to be honest, I think you're perfect
for each other.

34:46.502 --> 34:47.753
You'd make a great couple.

34:49.170 --> 34:52.466
She's got a great body.
You've seen it for yourself.

34:57.138 --> 34:59.473
She lost weight
and she has a really great figure.

35:04.520 --> 35:05.938
Your mother is very beautiful, but the idea

35:06.022 --> 35:08.107
that she and I could ever be together
is ludicrous.

35:09.108 --> 35:10.985
Let me remind you, I'm a married man.

35:11.944 --> 35:15.489
And I love my wife very much and my kids,
and that we are very happy together.

35:16.616 --> 35:18.993
And for your information,
you're absolutely fine.

35:19.076 --> 35:19.994
There's nothing wrong with you.

35:20.703 --> 35:23.581
But you really should stop smoking.
Do you promise?

35:25.291 --> 35:28.210
So we're okay?
There is nothing wrong with me?

35:29.420 --> 35:30.463
You couldn't be healthier.

35:31.756 --> 35:33.799
You should really go now
because I'm late for my rounds.

35:41.724 --> 35:46.270
Don't use that knife. Here.
Use this one. It's much sharper.

35:47.355 --> 35:49.482
- There you go, Doctor.
- Thank you, Nurse.

35:52.193 --> 35:55.237
Oh, and don't forget to slice off
the cheeks. They're delicious.

35:55.571 --> 35:56.614
I can do that.

36:02.912 --> 36:04.080
<i>Where are you?</i>

36:05.998 --> 36:08.542
<i>I called you a hundred times.
Didn't you see my calls?</i>

36:10.378 --> 36:11.587
<i>Yeah, I'm here.</i>

36:14.131 --> 36:17.510
<i>What do you mean you can't?
I got you a slice of apple pie.</i>

36:20.137 --> 36:24.100
No, no, you have to.
I've been waiting for over half an hour.

36:28.521 --> 36:32.692
Just come for a little while.
I can come closer to where you are.

36:33.567 --> 36:34.777
Are you at the hospital?

36:36.612 --> 36:38.322
I can bring you the apple pie.

36:40.282 --> 36:42.368
What's... what's so important?

36:44.245 --> 36:47.998
Is it a... is it an operation?
Are you at the hospital?

36:51.877 --> 36:53.713
I love the sound of those cooking.

37:04.849 --> 37:09.645
- Where were you?
- I was inside. Making a call.

37:10.896 --> 37:12.982
The fish is almost ready. Pass me your plate.

37:14.316 --> 37:16.569
I'll get them.
I need to wash my hands anyway.

37:17.361 --> 37:18.696
Thank you, my dear.

37:26.704 --> 37:29.206
- Do you need a hand?
- No, that's okay.

37:31.876 --> 37:34.253
I forgot to tell you
I saw that boy yesterday.

37:34.920 --> 37:36.297
Your daughter's school mate.

37:37.214 --> 37:38.132
Martin?

37:38.799 --> 37:42.261
Yes, right, Martin.
Couldn't remember his name.

37:43.721 --> 37:45.765
- Where did you see him?
- At the hospital.

37:46.390 --> 37:49.018
He was hanging around your car.
Looked like he was waiting for you.

37:49.977 --> 37:52.521
I tried to say hello
but he pretended not to see me.

37:52.855 --> 37:56.192
That's impossible. Can't have been him.

37:56.692 --> 37:59.111
I could be wrong,
but it looked a lot like him.

38:00.821 --> 38:04.158
Take my piece off the grill, will you?
I don't like it overdone.

38:19.882 --> 38:21.509
- Hi, Dad.
- Hello, darling.

38:22.092 --> 38:24.011
- Where have you been?
- Choir practice.

38:24.595 --> 38:26.806
- Have you eaten?
- Yes, I ate earlier.

38:27.306 --> 38:30.267
You don't have to take the dog for a walk.
I took her out already.

38:30.351 --> 38:32.228
- I got back a little while ago.
- Okay.

38:33.312 --> 38:34.855
Dad, do you know who I saw today?

38:35.397 --> 38:36.482
- Who, darling?
- Martin.

38:36.899 --> 38:37.817
Martin who?

38:38.067 --> 38:40.736
Martin, that boy who came over here
the other day.

38:41.237 --> 38:42.696
The son of your ex-patient.

38:43.364 --> 38:46.283
He brought me back from choir practice
on his friend's motorcycle.

38:46.784 --> 38:49.578
He's really funny.
I laughed so hard my ribs hurt.

38:51.163 --> 38:52.540
Yes, he is very funny.

38:54.333 --> 38:56.752
Kim, I don't want you riding
on motorcycles without a helmet.

38:57.002 --> 38:59.421
I was wearing a helmet. He gave me his.

38:59.839 --> 39:03.092
- Why didn't you ask him to come in?
- I did but he was in a hurry.

39:03.425 --> 39:04.552
He had to get home.

39:04.969 --> 39:06.720
- Where's Mom?
- She's taking a shower.

39:07.263 --> 39:08.389
Is there something you need?

39:09.974 --> 39:11.058
I'm going up to bed.

39:12.101 --> 39:13.102
Good night, darling.

40:08.157 --> 40:10.242
- Did you wake Bob?
- I did.

40:11.118 --> 40:13.579
He just likes lying in bed
before getting up. Leave him be.

40:14.371 --> 40:16.332
You want me to squeeze you
some more orange juice?

40:16.916 --> 40:18.542
He'll be late. Have you seen the time?

40:19.793 --> 40:21.211
School bus will be here any minute.

40:29.553 --> 40:32.348
Robert, do you have any idea
what time it is? Get up and get dressed.

40:35.309 --> 40:36.310
I can't get up.

40:36.769 --> 40:39.229
You have ten minutes to get washed,
dressed, and eat your breakfast.

40:39.855 --> 40:42.274
I'm not going to drive you to school,
and neither is your mother.

40:44.026 --> 40:45.027
I can't get up.

40:46.028 --> 40:48.113
Bob, get up and get dressed,
and stop messing around.

40:49.448 --> 40:53.118
Dad, my legs, they're numb.

40:54.828 --> 40:55.996
I can't move them.

40:58.499 --> 40:59.667
I can't stand up.

41:34.535 --> 41:36.078
<i>Do you know where you are right now?</i>

41:36.745 --> 41:39.415
I'm at the hospital,
in the neurology department.

41:39.957 --> 41:43.836
You are absolutely right.
Can you tell me what day it is today?

41:44.378 --> 41:46.338
- Thursday.
- Right again.

41:46.630 --> 41:48.549
Now, I'm going to take this pin,

41:49.133 --> 41:52.219
I'm going to touch the soles
of your feet and your toes

41:52.720 --> 41:55.139
and I want you to tell me...

41:56.265 --> 41:58.434
- Can you feel this?
- Yeah.

42:02.396 --> 42:03.897
Mm-hm. Yes.

42:04.314 --> 42:07.860
For this one, you're gonna sit up
and look right at me. Okay?

42:20.330 --> 42:22.166
Good. Now stick out your tongue...

42:37.598 --> 42:39.767
- What happened?
- Everything's absolutely fine.

42:40.225 --> 42:42.811
Larry gave him a thorough
neurological exam. It's nothing.

42:43.604 --> 42:45.564
You two go home. And we'll talk tonight.

42:46.190 --> 42:49.068
I won't be late.
My schedule today is pretty light. Okay?

42:49.943 --> 42:51.653
Maybe he should get an MRI.

42:52.279 --> 42:55.866
There's no need to bother with all that.
He just got scared, that's all.

42:57.409 --> 42:59.411
He's absolutely fine.
You're absolutely fine, aren't you?

42:59.495 --> 43:00.412
Yeah.

43:01.789 --> 43:03.248
I think maybe there was a test
at school today

43:03.332 --> 43:04.792
that we hadn't prepared for very well.

43:05.167 --> 43:08.003
Yes, he wanted to spend the day
at the hospital with Larry and us.

43:08.712 --> 43:09.630
Let's go.

43:10.172 --> 43:11.090
- Dad.
- Yeah?

43:11.381 --> 43:13.258
Aren't you going to show us
an operating theater?

43:13.342 --> 43:14.343
Another time, darling.

43:14.551 --> 43:16.095
They need me to prep for surgery right away.

43:16.178 --> 43:17.554
I have to go. I'll see you tonight.

43:48.669 --> 43:50.337
I can't feel my legs.

43:52.214 --> 43:53.674
- What?
- I can't feel my legs!

43:58.345 --> 43:59.596
Come on, roll over.

44:01.390 --> 44:03.267
Excuse me, can we get some help here?

44:04.935 --> 44:06.436
He needs some help. Thank you.

44:37.926 --> 44:42.222
<i>MRI, MRA both fine.
Blood work came back good.</i>

44:43.223 --> 44:45.767
<i>Cardiogram, chest X-ray, all clear.</i>

44:46.185 --> 44:49.479
<i>Has he been
under any psychological stress lately?</i>

44:49.938 --> 44:51.356
<i>Exams at school maybe?</i>

44:51.440 --> 44:54.109
- Yes.
- He's not stressed. He's fine.

44:54.568 --> 44:56.820
He's a little anxious
but that's just the way he is.

44:58.238 --> 45:01.533
In my opinion,
he should stay in tomorrow, as well,

45:01.617 --> 45:03.285
just so we can keep an eye on him.

45:03.702 --> 45:04.870
What about a PET scan?

45:05.162 --> 45:08.290
I don't think there's any need for that.
What do you think, Larry?

45:09.208 --> 45:11.168
And tomorrow he'll be well enough
to walk all the way home.

45:11.543 --> 45:13.670
Yes, I don't think
it's necessary at this point.

45:14.171 --> 45:18.050
Let's see how things go tomorrow
and we'll take it from there.

45:18.884 --> 45:20.886
There's nothing to worry about,
in my opinion.

45:21.470 --> 45:25.265
You go home, we'll speak tomorrow,
and I'll be here all day.

45:26.391 --> 45:29.102
And, Anna, great seeing you...

45:30.479 --> 45:31.772
even under these circumstances.

45:32.231 --> 45:34.274
- You, too, Larry.
- Good night.

45:34.775 --> 45:36.818
Goodbye, Larry. And thanks for everything.

45:37.819 --> 45:40.489
Do you want me to let them know
you won't be operating tomorrow?

45:40.572 --> 45:43.033
I said no. Stop going on about it.

45:43.367 --> 45:44.952
That won't be necessary, Matthew.

45:45.452 --> 45:47.412
I'll come by in the morning.
I won't go into the clinic.

45:47.496 --> 45:49.331
I'll bring in those doughnuts
he loves so much.

45:49.414 --> 45:51.750
Yes. I'm sure he'll be thrilled.

46:45.637 --> 46:48.348
- Where were you?
- At Claire's.

46:50.767 --> 46:52.853
- Is Dad asleep?
- Yes.

46:55.439 --> 46:58.567
- How's Bob?
- Bob is absolutely fine.

46:58.650 --> 47:00.402
They're just keeping him in as a precaution.

47:03.071 --> 47:06.450
- How are you feeling?
- I'm fine. How do you mean?

47:07.284 --> 47:10.495
- I mean, are you tired?
- I'm absolutely fine.

47:12.622 --> 47:14.708
- I'm a little tired, that's all.
- Okay.

47:18.128 --> 47:19.129
See you in the morning.

47:20.005 --> 47:22.632
Oh, and while Bob's in the hospital
you'll be responsible

47:22.716 --> 47:24.301
for watering the plants. Okay?

47:37.147 --> 47:39.358
Did he go to the bathroom? Did he get up?

47:39.441 --> 47:41.985
He hadn't when I passed by
about an hour ago. He didn't want to.

47:42.069 --> 47:43.737
He didn't want to pee or hadn't gotten up?

47:43.820 --> 47:46.031
- He didn't want to pee.
- Could he get up?

47:46.114 --> 47:47.949
He was asleep.
I didn't want to drag him out of bed.

47:53.330 --> 47:56.083
Good morning, Doctor.
How are you, Mrs. Murphy?

47:57.125 --> 48:00.170
I came by to see Bob.
Kim told me what happened.

48:01.213 --> 48:03.215
